{"word":"G139 - αἵρεσις - haíresis - hah'-ee-res-is - Heresy","slug":"G139","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">αἵρεσις</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>haíresis"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>hah'-ee-res-is"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Heresy"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x03B9;&#x0314;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03B5;&#x03C3;&#x03B9;&#x03C2; - hairesis</b> - <i>hah'ee-res-is</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G138\">G138</a>; properly a <i>choice</i>, that is, (specifically) a <i>party</i> or (abstractly) <i>disunion</i>. (&ldquo;heresy&rdquo; is the Greek word itself.): - heresy [which is the Greekord itself], sect."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1243\">G1243</a>, <a href=\"#/G1244\">G1244</a>, <a href=\"#/G138\">G138</a>, <a href=\"#/G140\">G140</a>, <a href=\"#/G141\">G141</a>"}]}